text: We have followed up 50 individuals in Group A and 45 in Group B. Baseline characteristics of these patients are shown in Table 1 . A total of 9 children in Group A and 5 in Group B were lost to follow up due to difficulties in phone contact and/or refusal to answer one or more study ques- tions. Characteristics from these patients were compared between groups, and were considered not to implicate in potential selection bias.
